						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">In NES games, no, not really. $20 and $30 are <em>supposed</em> to be the same white, and there are practical reasons why you might want to use $20 instead of $30. The main one I can think of is that it makes fading out look more natural when white doesn't persist for an extra step of the fadeout.</div><br /><br />Ah good point</div>

					
