						<div class="postbody">I was reading a bit about what &quot;official&quot; games were allowed to use and Jaws is a pretty rare case, apparently developers were asked not to use $30 because it caused problems with some CRT sets as it was &quot;whiter than white&quot; - indeed games would be rejected by Nintendo if they used #30. The same went for $0d as it was &quot;blacker than black&quot; (not sure what damage that could do though). $e &amp; $f range were not allowed either.<br /><br />Having trouble converting this for FCEUX (as it requires 8bit colour depth), which this is not. The quest ends here <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /></div>

					
